				<h2>About the Forum</h2>
				<p>
					The Global Methane, Climate and Clean Air Forum is a joint event sponsored by the
					Global Methane Initiative (GMI) and the Climate & Clean Air Coalition (CCAC). The Forum is a premier
					global event that brings together policy-makers, industry leaders, technical experts, and
					researchers from around the world to discuss opportunities to address methane emissions while
					advancing the recovery and use of methane as a valuable energy source.
				</p>
				<p>The 2022 Forum provides a unique opportunity for participants to access:</p>
					<ul>
						<li>High-level plenary sessions on cross-cutting issues including the benefits of fast action to
						reduce short-lived climate pollutants, national policy and planning, and financing for
						implementation</li>
						<li>Updates on new international efforts underway, such as the Global Methane Pledge and the Joint
						China-U.S. Declaration on Enhancing Climate Action</li>
						<li>Technical sessions on biogas (agricultural sources, municipal solid waste, municipal
						wastewater systems), coal mines, oil and natural gas systems, heavy duty vehicles, household
						energy (HHE), and hydrofluorocarbons (HFCs)</li>
						<li>GMI Subcommittee and CCAC Hub-led discussions on policy and projects</li>
						<li>Presentations about proven, innovative methane mitigation techniques and productive uses of
						recovered methane</li>
						<li>Opportunities for in-person networking with methane experts in the public and private sectors
						from around the world</li>
						<li>Optional site visits (e.g., landfill)</li>
					</ul>

